description:
Proper Japanese Title: 週刊少年ジャンプの増刊号

Quarterly specials for the series Weekly Shonen Jump, which began publication in the mid-80's. Though it featured one-shots in every special (often by creators who would go on to be some of the best-known of their era), it is also notable for serializing Bastard! after it was moved out of the main Weekly Shonen Jump magazine. After 1996, the seasonal specials ended and were replaced with Akamaru Jump (which only published three times a year, skipping the autumn special).
name: Weekly Shonen Jump Seasonal Special

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 少年ジャンプNEXT!

Jump Next! was the third iteration of a seasonal off-shoot of Weekly Shonen Jump directly replacing Akamaru Jump which lasted for over ten years. Originally it was a proper seasonal magazine, dating its issues by the seasons, but in 2014 it became a bimonthly, releasing six issues a year dated by the months.

Like its predecessors it was mainly a home for one-shots while also running a few of its own serials. Usually the covers were represented by series that had been extremely popular in Weekly Shonen Jump but it rarely can legitimate chapters from these titles. However, some series that would go on to be popular, were first published in one-shot form in this magazine, while a few long-running series that had been cancelled published their final chapters in this magazine.

After six years, the magazine ended and was replaced by Shonen Jump Giga.

Apart from various one-shots, ongoing serials from this magazine include:

  • Beelzebub Bangaihen
  • Kuroko no Basuke - Extra Game
  • Soul Catcher(S)
name: Jump Next!
